Former Free State Agriculture Department head Peter Thabethe returns to the state capture inquiry today. • Editor’s note: This livestream has ended. You can watch the recording above. JOHANNESBURG - Former Free State Department of Agriculture head Peter Thabethe returned to the state capture inquiry. Last week, Thabethe revealed that lack of planning compromised the Estina dairy farm project and wasted taxpayer's money. WATCH: Former FS Agriculture HOD continues testimony Thabethe's name has come up several times in the testimony from other witnesses on the Estina project. As HOD, he was the accounting officer at the time of the failed Gupta-linked project that was meant to empower emerging black farmers in the eastern Free State.  